==English==
===Noun===
'''Chinese truffle''' (''Plural:'' '''Chinese truffles''') 

#A species of [[truffle]], ''Tuber sinensis'' (sometimes called ''Tuber indicum''), native to China and harvested in quantity.  Unlike the european [[black truffle]] and [[white truffle]] it is not prized as a culinary ingredient and is considered to have bland taste and aroma and a chewy texture.  Sometimes fraudulently passed off as the black truffle it resembles.

See [[wikipedia:truffle]]